# Reusable practice architecture

Prefer shared infrastructure over duplicated per-lesson logic.

## Rules

- Use shared helpers/components for repeated behavior across lessons and subjects.
- Do not duplicate logic per lesson when a universal helper exists in `lib/`.
- New lesson types should reuse existing shared rendering, validation, autofocus, and review infrastructure where possible.
- Create a reusable helper when the same rule appears in more than one feature.
- Keep lesson files focused on configuration and content, not duplicated infrastructure.

## Examples

- Review timing → `lib/review/scheduler.ts`
- Answer validation → subject-specific `lib/` validators
- Autofocus → practice screen refs/effects + `.cursor/rules/practice-autofocus.mdc`
- Exercise generation → `lib/` generators + `data/` presets
